The paper deals with the loss surface of a feed-forward neural network with ReLU non-linearities, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and optimization. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also includes an experimental section on image classification, which suggests that it may belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper addresses an open problem given at the Conference on Learning Theory (COLT) 2015, which indicates that it may belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses weight decay regularization, which is a topic related to information theory and coding, suggesting that it may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory).
